{% import "macros.njk" as macro with context %}
{% slide %}
    <p><span data-annotate>So you want to be a web developer...</span></p>
    <p>What's that, you don't? Okay, no problem!</p>
    <p>This rough guide is going to have some information that's specific to the work of coding, but the most of this will apply to anyone looking to work on the web.</p>
{% endslide %}
{% slide %}
    <div class="related-post">
        <strong>Related post: <em>Different jobs in a web project</em></strong>
        <p>If you want to learn about all the many jobs & careers related to building stuff on the web, check out our related post:{% br %}<a class="related-post__link" href="/web-life-cycle/">Different jobs in a web project <img src="/images/page-link.svg" alt="Link to another page" class="related-post__icon" height="150" width="150"></a></p>
    </div>
{% endslide %}
{% slide %}
    <p>If you <em>do</em> want to write code for a living, however, let me congratulate you on a good career choice.</p>
    <p>There's good reason to believe that a coding career is {# {% ext "https://whoisnnamdi.com/never-enough-developers/" %}future-proof{% endext %} #}{% ext "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=29808376" %}future-proof{% endext %}, {% ext "https://www.indeed.com/career-advice/finding-a-job/recession-proof-industries" %}recession-proof{% endext %}, and a pretty good job to have when {% ext "https://medium.com/coderbyte/how-the-covid-19-pandemic-is-impacting-software-development-hiring-72243f41ac9e" %}everyone suddenly needs to work at home for a few years{% endext %}.</p>
{% endslide %}
{% slide %}
    <p>Over the past decade, the demand for people who can code for the web has skyrocketed. Coding "boot camps" have sprung up, offering to teach you the latest skills in a matter of months, with a focus on what employers are looking for in the moment.</p>
    <p>These boot camps have increased the signal-to-noise ratio for recruiters, making it harder to distinguish candidates with working knowledge from those who have only a superficial grasp on a concept.</p>
    <p>As a result, it has become somewhat harder to get your foot in the door, particularly for those just starting out, and especially in remote-only work.</p>
{% endslide %}
{% slide %}
    <p>Don't let this discourage you, though. The government (where I am, in Canada), has 'web developer' as a top-rated job prospect for the next ten years in the majority of provinces.</p>
    <figure>
        {% ext "https://explore-labour-market.service.canada.ca/viz?page=outlooks&lang=en&noc=2175&geo=0&view=#4/60.45/-89.08" %}{% image "images/prospects.png", "Map showing web developer job propect ratings by province, with all provinces rated 2 out of three or 3 out of three.", "(min-width: 30em) 1200px, 100vw", "Map via explore-labour-market.service.canada.ca" %}{% endext %}
        <figcaption>Via {% ext "https://www.jobbank.gc.ca/marketreport/outlook-occupation/17892/ca" %}jobbank.gc.ca{% endext %}</figcaption>
    </figure>
{% endslide %}
{% slide %}
    <blockquote><p>"The skills typically required in this occupation are usually standard worldwide... [a]s a result, there are lower barriers for immigrants to become web designers and developers... simplifying their entry and permanency in the country."</p><footer><cite>{% ext "https://www.jobbank.gc.ca/marketreport/outlook-occupation/17892/ca#:~:text=The%20skills%20typically,in%20the%20country." %}Government of Canada: Job Bank{% endext %}</cite></footer></blockquote>
{% endslide %}
{% slide %}
    <p>I love that the web is providing jobs that provide a decent living (even to weirdos like me), and help establish people who want to come live where I am!</p>
    <p>Okay, so how do you actually <em>get</em> one of these jobs? Let's start by figuring out <span data-annotate data-ann-color="var(--alert)">what skills you need</span>, and how to get them.</p>
{% endslide %}
